<subSubSection id="C32B657DFFB5FF81099EFC11FE44FEF9" pageId="15" pageNumber="86" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8E36F6FFB5FF81099EFC11FE44FEF9" blockId="15.[151,1436,151,321]" pageId="15" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B945EAE4FFB5FF81099EFC11FE89FEA5" bold="true" box="[199,334,259,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="86">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B945EAE4FFB5FF810A02FC11FC51FEA4" box="[859,918,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="86">mini-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B945EAE4FFB5FF810A94FC11FBCDFEA5" box="[973,1034,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="86">lobus</emphasis>
, referring to the small anellar lobes in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
